title: Jamari Peacock rushes for three TDs to power Yulee past Bishop Kenny
text:
Jamari Peacock rushes for three TDs to power Yulee past Bishop Kenny 
Sat, Oct 10, 2015 @ 12:29 am 
YULEE 38 
BISHOP KENNY 24 
Star of the game: Junior running back Jamari Peacock rushed for a game-high 128 yards on 20 carries, scored three touchdowns and added three two-point conversion runs to power Yulee to a non-district victory at Bishop Kenny. 
Turning point: After the Crusaders (3-3) cut the lead to 30-24 with 2:06 left in the game, Peacock rambled 43 yards untouched up the middle on a touchdown run to seal the win for Yulee. Peacock rushed for 95 yards and two TDs in the fourth quarter. 
On defense: Kaleb Graves and Antwaun Alexander had interceptions for Yulee, and Chris Roberts had a sack and fumble recovery. ... Michael Munder and Kyle Cusick led Bishop Kenny with seven tackles each. 
Fast facts: Yulee (3-3) outscored Bishop Kenny 22-3 in the second quarter to grab a 22-10 lead at halftime. ... The Hornets forced four turnovers. ... Marquez Wells had two fourth-quarter TD receptions for BK. ... Aaron Fudge caught six passes for 87 yards for Bishop Kenny, which plays at Ponte Vedra next Friday. 
They said it: ”After losing three games in a row, we needed a win,” said Yulee coach Bobby Ramsay, whose team hosts Stanton next week. “This was our biggest win for us since Derrick Henry graduated.” Dennis Bergin For the Times-Union
